  "prompt": "Can I import a car from Dubai to the USA?",
  "response": "Yes, you can import a car from Dubai to the USA, but there are several important requirements and steps:\n\n1. Vehicle Eligibility\n- Must be at least 25 years old to import without DOT/EPA compliance\n- Newer vehicles must meet specific US safety and emissions standards\n\n2. Required Documentation\n- Original title\n- Bill of sale\n- UAE registration\n- Certificate of Origin\n- Import/export customs documents\n\n3. Customs and Fees\n- Pay import duties (typically 2.5% for cars)\n- Pay customs clearance fees\n- Pay EPA and DOT compliance fees\n- Potential additional state taxes/registration fees\n\n4. Compliance Inspections\n- Vehicle must pass EPA and DOT inspections\n- May require modifications to meet US standards\n- Professional import/export companies can help navigate this process\n\n5. Shipping Options\n- Container shipping\n- Roll-on/Roll-off (RoRo) shipping\n\n6. Additional Considerations\n- Total costs can be significant\n- Insurance and transportation\n- Potential language translation requirements\n- Potential need for mechanical/structural modifications\n\n7. Recommended Steps\n- Work with a professional import/export company\n- Research specific model's import eligibility\n- Get comprehensive cost estimates",
